## Quick start

```bash
make tidy
make run
```

Open `http://localhost:8080/api/v1/health` for the liveness probe and
`http://localhost:8080/api/v1/items` for the CRUD surface.

## Testing & coverage

```bash
make test   # go test -race -cover + --fail-under 70 (X1 Go threshold)
```

Coverage threshold matches `COVERAGE_THRESHOLDS["go"]` in
`backend.software_simulator` — see the OmniSight X1 simulate-track docs
for why 70% is the floor on Go.

## Container & k8s

```bash
make docker
docker compose up -d

make helm       # helm lint + package
```

## Multi-platform release (goreleaser)

```bash
make release-check        # goreleaser check (offline validation)
make release-snapshot     # builds Linux/Darwin/Windows × amd64/arm64 under dist/
```

Wired to `backend.build_adapters.GoreleaserAdapter` (X3 #299).

## X4 compliance gates

```bash
python -m backend.software_compliance --app-path .
```

The shipped `spdx.allowlist.json` denies GPL/AGPL by default. Adjust
the allowlist if a dependency needs a waiver — log the waiver in the
project's role skill.
